Decides whether this service is allowed to participate in SSO.
Decides whether all attributes AND corresponding values should be evaluated before access can be granted. If left unchecked, the first successful match on attribute name and value will allow access.
URL to which CAS should direct in the event that service access is defined.
List of authentication providers this services is allowed to delegate authentication to.
Location where the groovy script file to determine granting access to this service is loaded

This access strategy attempts to locate Grouper groups for the CAS principal. The groups returned by Grouper are collected as CAS attributes and examined against the list of required attributes for service access.
URL that CAS should contact to determine if access to this service should be granted.
Acceptable HTTP codes before granting access to this service.
Indicates whether matching on required attribute values should be done in a case-insensitive manner.
Determines whether this service is allowed to use surrogate authentication.
List of attributes and values that must be present for the primary user in order to allow surrogate authentication.
Determines the starting date/time from which service access is allowed.
Determines the ending date/time from which service access is allowed.
List of WS Federation Claims that will be mapped to the corresponding attribute from the attributes repository.
Exclude default bundle of attributes for release
Indicates whether global and default attributes set to release to all applications should be excluded for release for this specific application.
Authorized to release to credential password
Release credential password to the application?
Authorized to release proxy granting ticket ID
Release proxy-granting ticket id to the application?

Determines whether this policy should exclude the authentication/protocol attributes for release. Authentication attributes are considered those that are not tied to a specific principal and define extra supplamentary metadata about the authentication event itself, such as the commencement date.
Control whether consent is active/inactive for this service.
Exclude the indicated attributes from consent.
Force-include the indicated attributes in consent, provided attributes are resolved.
A regex pattern used to filter attributes based on their values only. Values that successfully pass the filter will be available for release to the application.
This field can accept either an inline groovy script that will be executed or a location of an external script file that will be loaded and executed.
Indicates whether unmapped attributes should be removed from the final bundle.
Indicates whether pattern-matching should execute over the entire value region.
Time unit of measure for the cache expiration policy.

Decides how attributes that are retrieved from the cache should be merged into the existing attribute repository. Attributes may be replaced, ignored or contain multiple values as a result of the merge action.
Location of a script file that can be triggered to determine which attributes can be released.
List of resolved attributes out of the available collection of attributes from the attribute repository. Select attributes that are allowed to be released to the application
The EntityId for the SP providing the metadata attributes.
Format description for the entity attribute. This field is optional.
List of attributes that are defined as part of the SP Metadata.
The URL of the REST endpoint that will be called to retrieve a list of attributes that will be released.
Location of a groovy script file that can be triggered by the server to determine the attributes to be released.
Location of groovy script file that will be used by this service to determine if MFA is triggered when accessing this service.
List of multifactor provider ids to assign to this service.
Decide what CAS should do in the event that a provider is not available.
Principal attribute name to trigger MFA when accessing this service.
Principal attribute value to match in order to trigger MFA when accessing this service.
Bypass multifactor authentication for this service.

The logo representing this service that would be displayed on the login page. Could be a file/classpath path or an actual http url.
Decides whether access to this service is authorized by CAS.
Determines how CAS should load, sort and evaluate services per this numeric order.

The date on which the registration record is deemed expired. The expiration date may be specified in 2011-12-03T10:15:30, 09/24/1980 04:30 PM, 09/24/2014 6:30 AM, 09/24/2013 18:45, 09/24/2017 or 2017-10-25 formats.
When true, removes the application from the CAS service registry if and when expired. Otherwise the application record will be marked as disabled.
Notifiy contacts when service is deleted

Notifies contacts of the application via email or text, assuming valid contacts with email addresses or phone numbers are defined and CAS is configured to send email messages or SMS notifications. The notification is only sent if the application is expired and is about to be deleted from the registry.
Url where logout requests will be sent to, for this service.
Defines how CAS should execute logout operations when dealing with this service.
OAuth client id for this OAuth client. Only applies to OAuth service types.
Secret key for this OAuth client. Only applies to OAuth service types.
Enable to show your OAuth Client Secret.
Indicates whether the OAuth confirmation screen should be displayed before accessing the service application.
Indicates whether a refresh token should be generated with the access token for this OAuth client.
Indicates whether the access token response should be in JSON format or in plain text.

Secret key for this OIDC client. Only applies to OIDC service types.
Enable to show your OIDC Client Secret.
Indicates whether the OIDC confirmation screen should be displayed before accessing the service application.
Indicates whether a refresh token should be generated with the access token for this OIDC client.
Location of the JSON web keystore to sign id tokens with.
List any custom defined scopes that should be released.
Whether ID tokens should be signed.
Indicates whether this service should support the implicit flow.
Whether ID tokens should be encrypted.
Encryption algorithm to use with ID tokens.
Encryption content encoding algorithm to use with ID tokens.
Type to use when generating principal identifiers. Default is public.
Host value of this URL is used as the sector identifier for the pairwise identifier calculation. If left undefined, the host value of the serviceId will be used instead.
Matches the proxy callback url against a regex pattern. A successful match will authorize proxy authentication.

The location to the public key file used to authenticate and sign the CAS response. This is specifically used to encrypt and sign the credential and the proxy granting ticket returned directly in the CAS validation response, provided the service is authorized to release those attributes.
Represents a public key for a CAS registered service, used to encrypt credentials, proxy granting ticket ids for release.

Collection of authentication handler ids defined in the CAS server configuration that indicate the set of authentication handlers that must successfully execute before access to this service can be granted.
'Defines how CAS should respond to requests for this service.
Metadata location for this particular service provider.
Indicates how long should metadata be considered valid.
Location of the metadata signing public key so its authenticity can be verified.
If defined, will expire metadata in the cache after the indicated duration which will force CAS to retrieve and resolve the metadata again.
Regex applied to entity ids in a metadata aggregate.
Whether to include/exclude entity ids that match the filter pattern.
Whitelisted roles to keep in the metadata.
Controls whether to keep entities descriptors that contain no entity descriptors
Controls whether to keep entity descriptors that contain no roles.
Force the indicated Name ID format in the final SAML response.
Overwrite the SPNameQualifier attribute of the produced subject name id.
Overwrite the NameQualifier attribute of the produced subject name id.
Whether generation of a name identifier should be skipped for assertions
Whether generation of the InResponseTo element should be skipped for subject confirmations.
Whether generation of the NotOnOrAfter element should be skipped for subject confirmations.
Whether generation of the Recipient element should be skipped for subject confirmations.
Whether generation of the NotBefore element should be skipped for subject confirmations.

This setting controls the type of the signature block produced in the final SAML response for this application. The latter, being the default, encodes the signature in PEM format inside a X509Data block while the former encodes the signature based on the resolved public key under a DEREncodedKeyValue block.
The authentication context class that may be passed to the service provider. If none is defined here forcefully, metadata will be consulted instead.
Comma-separated list of audience urls to include in the assertion, in addition to the entity id.

A token that represents the theme that should be applied to CAS when this service asks for authentication. Valid values are a theme name configured in the CAS deployment, a REST endpoint or a groovy file location.

The realm identifier of the application, identified via the wtrealm parameter. This needs to match the realm defined for the identity provider. By default it’s set to the realm defined for the CAS identity provider.
Controls to whom security tokens apply. Defaults to the realm.
